metadata.name: "THIS SHIT GO HARD"
metadata.description:
ATOM PROJECT

Thus he was,

For he spoke on his hand,

That he would never leave.

So he was,

For he called.

What he saw?

With no sight—no word.

But he saw the light and saw the dawn.

Through no sound he could find.

But he saw the light and saw the dawn.

He thought of his own vision, and then thought—

And thought as he heard.

And so he heard.

But he saw the light and saw the dawn.

And so he saw.

He felt his own light.

He understood his own light.

And knew it with all its power.

He took, that he knew.

And he knew because he knew,

Because he was.

The first time he saw the light—the first time he saw the dawn—before his own vision:

In that moment his sight was opened:

The first to the heavens, while he was,

As he was, a second, the fourth he was:

Of that which I was!

Of that whose heart I was!

Of that who had never seen me: (I am, you are, you lie,

You deceive me—!
